reviews.author: Tara Seleen
reviews.text: Sandy beach, safe to swim. Can rent 2 chairs & umbrella for 30 soles, totally worth it. Worth a taxi ride if you want to swim at the beach. There are some free showers near a fenced in soccer field. Bathrooms cost 1 sole, bring your own toilet paper.

reviews.author: Shawna Fiscus
reviews.text: Nice beach with different activities to do other than just beach sitting, even in the Peruvian winter!

reviews.author: Tony G
reviews.text: You get molested by approx. 25 vendors per hour. Also crowded, noisy and full with trash. At least the sand is nice. And during weekdays you might have more peace.

reviews.author: Roger Hollingshead
reviews.text: This beach is amazing we had some of the best times jumping the waves. The waves were nearly 15 feet high and perfect for surfing there were many people here but it felt very private if you rent an umbrella for a very small amount of soles you can have your own two chairs and you get beer with it. I would totally come back to this beach someday I hope to be able to return and tour the city more than I got to in the two weeks I was just there. I definitely plan on returning to Surf this beach again.

reviews.text: Nice little cozy beach, outside of the crowded area of Barranco or Miraflores! You have to pay few soles to rent a chair, but it worth it if you plan to stay for a little while at the beach! Also different sellers are walking around but are not so annoying. Good place to swim, altought the waves were pretty rough the day we went!

reviews.text: One of the sandy beaches! Lovely restaurants with the most fresh and delicious fish.

reviews.text: Very locals

reviews.author: Jacolo10
reviews.text: Great for sports, the sea is very calm. You can find many paddle tennis shops. I went on a Monday and the place was packed, so I can't even imagine what it's like on a weekend. At night, many people stay around, making bonfires or drinking.

reviews.author: walter gonz√°lez
reviews.text: A small, sandy beach, about 100 meters wide, located between the Regatas Club and the Chorrillos fishing pier. Its waters are very calm, ideal for swimming, paddleboarding, and kayaking. **Update May 25: The beach has been renovated by the municipality. There is no longer vehicle access, but pedestrian access is available through the fishing terminal. The terminal is open and vehicles can enter, but the access is under construction. Paddleboard and kayak rentals are no longer available. The restaurants have been removed. Group boat tours are available from the pier. Fishing is allowed from the pier, and fishing tackle vendors are available.

reviews.text: It is a nice beach because there is no noise, few people, but it is paid, there is no security, and there is garbage

reviews.author: Giancarlo Mansilla
reviews.text: The beach is fair to difficult to access from the green coast. It is better to go in a group, never alone. There are a couple of stalls to buy food and drinks. I do not recommend going into the water, the waves break very hard on the shore and although it may not seem like it, it is very dangerous, as a result I have a fracture in my foot and I will be on crutches for a month. Very nice views, but excessively dangerous beach.

reviews.author: Jorge Gonzalez
reviews.text: Difficult to access, but a beautiful spot. No security personnel were seen around, but if you go with friends during the day, it shouldn't be a problem. Coarse sand, dunes, beautiful views, and a beautiful sunset.

reviews.author: Walter Vegazo Muro
reviews.text: A very nice beach, quite pleasant to spend time with the whole family, it has plenty of security and a place to park your cars.

reviews.author: Efrain Gabriel Marquina Ruiz
reviews.text: A beach with strong waves. Ideal for a morning jog. Opposite it is a promenade with areas for outdoor sports, a synthetic running track, and a bike path. Toward the end, rock formations give it an attractive atmosphere. It's recommended to go in a group, as it's safe there.

reviews.author: Thilo Boeck
reviews.text: Calm water and rather clean beach during weekdays. In summer it gets really crowded but nice and relaxed

reviews.author: Marco
reviews.text: Nice beach and fish market

reviews.author: Francisco R-58
reviews.text: A very nice place. The municipality organizes sports activities. It's recommended to go in the mornings rather than in the afternoons. Although there aren't many restaurants nearby, the only one is the seafood restaurant next door. If you want to eat something else, you have to walk up several blocks to barely find a restaurant. And at the main entrance, on the left side as you enter, there's a very, very neglected area.

reviews.author: Alexander Geyrhofer
reviews.text: I can't understand anyone who likes the beach.  Firstly, right on the street, crowded and extremely loud. Apparently everyone wants to be the best DJ and turns up the boombox, regardless of whether anyone wants to hear it or not. Umbrella costs 30 soles per day. Some beach vendor is shouting every minute. So you can't relax there.

reviews.author: Miguel Mej√≠a Castro
reviews.text: One of Peru's most beautiful popular beaches. It's part of the Costa Verde circuit, and I recommend visiting Monday through Friday, starting at 4 p.m., as it's very crowded on Saturdays and Sundays. Photo: @miguelmejiacastro

reviews.author: A Aguirre
reviews.text: Really cold water on a cloudy day. Hard to access because of stairways. Needs more upkeep

reviews.author: Fernando Augusto Sanchez
reviews.text: This beach is private...it is located behind the Morro, and can be reached via the Spider Pass, which is reached by walking along the rugged coast from the Horseshoe, bordering the cliffs of the Morro...on this beach there are vestiges of a tower from the time of the war between Chile and Peru...

reviews.author: Raul Hayball
reviews.text: The route to La Chira via La Herradura beach is adventurous and of medium risk. The beach itself is pretty, clean, the sea is rough. I haven't seen any swimmers. It doesn't have any services and the AAHH population is at the back on the hill. I don't know how safe it is.

reviews.author: Edgar Poe
reviews.text: An adventure to get to this beach, I definitely had a lot of fun

reviews.author: Ricardo Respaldiza
reviews.text: I went for a run on this beach and spent a pleasant moment of peace and tranquility. The sound of the beautiful sea and the absence of people allows it to be clean.
